data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's what changes and the fixes:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func`, not `Expression<Func>`

Your expression-tree building code **won't compile**. The new overload accepts a plain lambda with imperative control flow:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` plumbing.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö two changes

**a) Sibling complex types with same property names now get uniquified** (e.g. `Street` ŌåÆ `Street`, `Street1`). To keep your existing schema, pin column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path** ŌĆö `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

If you don't pin these, a migration will generate column renames (or worse, data loss if applied carelessly).

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText (redacted) for logging instead of command.CommandText
    }
}
```

Update **all** interface methods (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
